@bdowling I don't think the spec object is pickleable. A common pattern is to do one or both of the following:

1) memoize creating the client with something like [lru_cache](https://docs.python.org/3/library/functools.html#functools.lru_cache)
2) store the swagger json file locally, and load it with `SwaggerClient.from_spec`. This at least saves on the network call.

